WEBVTT

1
00:00:35.791 --> 00:00:37.208
I think we can all agree

2
00:00:37.291 --> 00:00:39.166
that things were better
under the Empire.

3
00:00:40.041 --> 00:00:43.250
Fortunately. I am still here
to protect you.

4
00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:46.916
Your communities can thrive
under my protection.

5
00:00:48.125 --> 00:00:50.083
You are the lucky few.

6
00:00:51.125 --> 00:00:53.458
But that which I provide
is expensive.

7
00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.750
And now
I must maintain all of it

8
00:00:56.833 --> 00:00:58.458
without the Empire's support

9
00:00:58.541 --> 00:01:00.791
until the galaxy realizes
what they've lost

10
00:01:01.541 --> 00:01:03.041
and demand our return.

11
00:01:04.375 --> 00:01:06.625
Long live the Empire.

12
00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:11.500
Long live the Empire.

13
00:01:13.416 --> 00:01:14.416
Good.

14
00:01:15.458 --> 00:01:16.750
Now for the bad news.

15
00:01:18.791 --> 00:01:20.666
I am raising your tribute.

16
00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:24.791
But...

17
00:01:24.875 --> 00:01:28.541
But. Your Excellency.
we are operating at a loss.

18
00:01:30.333 --> 00:01:33.416
The trade routes are plagued
with pirates and thieves.

19
00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:34.625
ready to attack at...

20
00:01:38.791 --> 00:01:41.041
Are you saying
that my protection is lacking?

21
00:01:41.833 --> 00:01:43.916
No. Your Excellency.

22
00:01:45.666 --> 00:01:47.875
I-I am saying that. uh...

23
00:01:52.375 --> 00:01:55.250
Perhaps you should all go
back to your townships

24
00:01:56.041 --> 00:01:57.750
and focus on solutions.

25
00:01:58.875 --> 00:02:00.291
not excuses.

26
00:02:02.291 --> 00:02:03.625
Does that sound reasonable?

27
00:02:09.208 --> 00:02:11.083
Sounds like a perimeter alarm.

28
00:02:11.166 --> 00:02:13.000
I'll confirm.

29
00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.750
-I've lost contact.
-Go check it.

30
00:02:20.791 --> 00:02:22.333
There's nothing to worry about.

31
00:02:22.416 --> 00:02:24.666
I'll send for reinforcements.

32
00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.875
I will require
a revenue projection...

33
00:02:53.625 --> 00:02:55.666
<i>We need backup. On the double!</i>

34
00:02:55.750 --> 00:02:56.750
Code Red.

35
00:03:04.041 --> 00:03:05.125
Lay down cover fire.

36
00:03:07.416 --> 00:03:08.666
Take up arms!

37
00:03:22.625 --> 00:03:24.416
Long live the Empire!

38
00:05:07.791 --> 00:05:10.000
What are you waiting for?
Hop on.

39
00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:27.666
Hang on.

40
00:05:54.291 --> 00:05:55.291
Did we get him?

41
00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:56.791
Not yet. sir. But we will.

42
00:06:05.041 --> 00:06:07.708
-We missed him! He's under us.
<i>-We have him.</i>

43
00:06:07.791 --> 00:06:08.791
<i>Fire.</i>

44
00:06:53.833 --> 00:06:55.916
<i>What's going on?
Give me a status report.</i>

45
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.541
<i>Has the target been eliminated?</i>

46
00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:59.833
-We've lost contact.
-Walker Three is gone.

47
00:07:00.458 --> 00:07:02.666
<i>-Send everybody!</i>
-Understood.

48
00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:03.958
Prepare to engage!

49
00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:13.916
Get ready. Weapons up.

50
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.500
Full barrel. Now. let's go.

51
00:07:50.541 --> 00:07:52.208
<i>Give me a status update.</i>

52
00:07:52.291 --> 00:07:54.541
<i>Did you see him?
Have you located him?</i>

53
00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.208
<i>Did you get The Mandalorian?</i>

54
00:07:59.458 --> 00:08:00.458
Something's up there.

55
00:08:02.625 --> 00:08:03.958
He's on the roof!

56
00:08:04.625 --> 00:08:05.625
<i>Can you see him?</i>

57
00:08:06.291 --> 00:08:07.291
<i>Take him out!</i>

58
00:08:07.375 --> 00:08:08.375
Get up there.

59
00:08:09.166 --> 00:08:10.291
But we're pilots.

60
00:08:10.375 --> 00:08:13.083
-Go now! Do it!
-Yes. sir. On our way.

61
00:08:13.166 --> 00:08:14.500
Get up there.

62
00:08:15.666 --> 00:08:16.666
Set the charges.

63
00:08:16.750 --> 00:08:18.166
-Prepare for exfil.
-Sir.

64
00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:21.625
<i>He's breaching the hatch.
He's breaching the hatch!</i>

65
00:08:39.375 --> 00:08:40.375
Autopilot.

66
00:09:13.291 --> 00:09:15.208
I know. I know.
I need to get the shot.

67
00:09:45.291 --> 00:09:47.958
You know. it's better
if you bring 'em in alive.

68
00:09:55.041 --> 00:09:56.041
You okay?

69
00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:00.875
You see. you catch the bad guy

70
00:10:00.958 --> 00:10:03.333
and they tell us
where the other bad guys are.

71
00:10:04.041 --> 00:10:05.791
Things went a little sideways.

72
00:12:26.666 --> 00:12:29.458
Good luck. You're gonna need it.

73
00:12:37.958 --> 00:12:40.625
Messy. Very messy.

74
00:12:41.916 --> 00:12:44.541
It was the best I could do
under the circumstances.

75
00:12:45.541 --> 00:12:47.541
The problem is.
we need information.

76
00:12:48.416 --> 00:12:50.309
Without it. we're never gonna
get to the bottom of

77
00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:52.166
what the Empire's up to.

78
00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:53.250
Just give me time.

79
00:12:53.333 --> 00:12:55.833
I'll take out every bad guy
in your deck of cards.

80
00:12:55.916 --> 00:12:57.458
This isn't about revenge.

81
00:12:57.958 --> 00:13:00.583
It's about
preventing another war...

82
00:13:03.833 --> 00:13:06.500
and protecting everything
the Rebellion fought for.

83
00:13:06.583 --> 00:13:08.791
Does that mean I'm not
getting paid for this one?

84
00:13:10.583 --> 00:13:12.416
You're getting paid all right.

85
00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:13.500
Come with me.

86
00:13:22.833 --> 00:13:24.041
Impressive.

87
00:13:24.125 --> 00:13:25.458
Where did you get one of these?

88
00:13:26.166 --> 00:13:28.291
It was from
a captured Imperial commandant

89
00:13:28.375 --> 00:13:30.625
who had a big collection
of vintage vehicles.

90
00:13:31.125 --> 00:13:33.750
This one is stock.
Perfectly restored.

91
00:13:34.416 --> 00:13:36.125
I took it out for a test spin.

92
00:13:36.708 --> 00:13:38.625
They did a nice job
on the rebuild.

93
00:13:41.333 --> 00:13:43.041
This is worth a lot more than

94
00:13:43.125 --> 00:13:44.625
the bounty on that Imp.

95
00:13:44.708 --> 00:13:47.333
Well. let's call it an advance
on the next mission.

96
00:13:49.583 --> 00:13:50.708
What next mission?

97
00:13:51.375 --> 00:13:52.833
Commander Coin.

98
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:55.333
Our missing Ace of Staves.

99
00:13:57.750 --> 00:13:59.416
No one knows what he looks like

100
00:13:59.500 --> 00:14:01.541
and most believe him to be dead.

101
00:14:02.250 --> 00:14:05.000
Not a lot to go on.
What's the play?

102
00:14:05.083 --> 00:14:08.250
I want you to go to Nal Hutta
and meet with the Hutts.

103
00:14:08.833 --> 00:14:10.791
They've agreed to
lead us to him.

104
00:14:10.875 --> 00:14:11.875
What's in it for them?

105
00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.833
Their nephew's being held
against his will

106
00:14:14.916 --> 00:14:17.416
by another crime syndicate
on the Outer Rim.

107
00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:18.708
and they need a professional

108
00:14:18.791 --> 00:14:20.375
to get him out
quickly and quietly.

109
00:14:20.458 --> 00:14:21.458
Where is he?

110
00:14:21.958 --> 00:14:23.416
They'll only tell you in person.

111
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:25.250
You got a name?

112
00:14:25.958 --> 00:14:27.583
His name is Rotta the Hutt.

113
00:14:27.666 --> 00:14:31.083
The only surviving heir
of crime lord Jabba the Hutt.

114
00:14:31.666 --> 00:14:32.916
You ever cross his path?

115
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.625
I tried not to.

116
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:36.833
So...

117
00:14:37.708 --> 00:14:38.833
do we have a deal?

118
00:14:38.916 --> 00:14:41.291
I only hunt down
Imperial war criminals.

119
00:14:41.375 --> 00:14:44.833
I don't work for gangsters
anymore. especially the Hutts.

120
00:14:44.916 --> 00:14:47.416
That's right. you don't.
You work for us.

121
00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:50.333
And right now. this is
what we need you to do.

122
00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:53.958
You don't want the job.
I got nothing for you.

123
00:15:05.750 --> 00:15:06.791
Come aboard.

124
00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:10.833
May as well have a look around.

125
00:15:15.791 --> 00:15:17.333
Let's go hear the Hutts out.

126
00:15:17.958 --> 00:15:19.958
I'll even let you fly this time.

127
00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:22.416
I didn't say yes.

128
00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:24.166
You didn't say no either.

129
00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:48.666
She's stock. but she's clean.

130
00:16:05.541 --> 00:16:07.291
Hey.

131
00:16:07.375 --> 00:16:08.583
Don't touch anything.

132
00:16:09.125 --> 00:16:10.458
Never touch the buttons.

133
00:17:54.125 --> 00:17:56.166
<i>Identify yourself.</i>

134
00:17:57.458 --> 00:17:59.916
<i>Razor Crest.</i>
requesting clearance.

135
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
I'm here
by invitation of the Twins.

136
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:06.333
Easy on the sticks.
They're expecting us.

137
00:18:07.041 --> 00:18:08.291
We should be fine.

138
00:18:10.708 --> 00:18:12.416
<i>Clearance granted.</i>

139
00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:13.875
<i>You are clear to approach.</i>

140
00:18:14.708 --> 00:18:16.750
They've got
a lot of firepower here.

141
00:18:16.833 --> 00:18:19.958
Yeah. Looks like
they hired the Droid Gotra.

142
00:18:20.041 --> 00:18:22.041
The Hutts
take security seriously.

143
00:19:13.125 --> 00:19:15.017
The Hutts have been the
head of criminal enterprises

144
00:19:15.041 --> 00:19:16.583
for thousands of years.

145
00:19:21.083 --> 00:19:23.041
They use violence and treachery

146
00:19:23.125 --> 00:19:24.333
to maintain control.

147
00:19:26.083 --> 00:19:27.458
Be careful.

148
00:19:27.541 --> 00:19:32.125
We may be their guests.
but we are not safe.

149
00:20:16.125 --> 00:20:19.375
We finally meet the legendary Mandalorian.

150
00:20:20.583 --> 00:20:25.000
We are so glad you agreed to work for us.

151
00:20:25.583 --> 00:20:27.833
You will be very rich.

152
00:20:27.916 --> 00:20:29.458
I don't work for you.

153
00:20:29.541 --> 00:20:31.041
I work for the New Republic.

154
00:20:31.916 --> 00:20:33.000
I'm told you can lead us

155
00:20:33.083 --> 00:20:35.375
to the Imperial fugitive
Commander Coin.

156
00:20:36.250 --> 00:20:38.500
Of course. Mando.

157
00:20:38.583 --> 00:20:40.333
I understand your nephew. Rotta.

158
00:20:40.416 --> 00:20:41.708
has been kidnapped.

159
00:20:42.041 --> 00:20:45.083
Yes. our poor nephew has been taken.

160
00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:48.625
He fell in with a bad crowd.

161
00:20:49.041 --> 00:20:51.708
We are heartbroken.

162
00:20:52.458 --> 00:20:55.208
Think of how you would feel

163
00:20:55.291 --> 00:20:58.375
if your little one went missing.

164
00:21:00.666 --> 00:21:02.166
What does he look like?

165
00:21:02.250 --> 00:21:03.458
Do you have an image?

166
00:21:03.750 --> 00:21:05.083
Ah. yes.

167
00:21:05.583 --> 00:21:09.375
The only image we have is from long ago.

168
00:21:15.958 --> 00:21:19.666
He's had a growth spurt since then.

169
00:21:20.416 --> 00:21:24.000
Okay. I'll rescue your nephew.

170
00:21:24.083 --> 00:21:25.083
Where is he being held?

171
00:21:25.750 --> 00:21:30.666
You will find him on the moon of Shakari.

172
00:21:31.250 --> 00:21:32.666
It shall be done.

173
00:21:52.166 --> 00:21:53.916
We're about to
come out of hyperspace

174
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.333
in the Shakari system.

175
00:21:55.958 --> 00:21:58.125
<i>To state
the obvious. you are operating</i>

176
00:21:58.208 --> 00:22:00.375
<i>outside the jurisdiction
of the New Republic.</i>

177
00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:05.375
If things get messy. I can't
call in an X-wing strike.

178
00:22:05.916 --> 00:22:07.791
I know the drill.

179
00:22:08.666 --> 00:22:12.291
Before going into harm's way.
check your armor first.

180
00:22:12.375 --> 00:22:14.833
It's gotta fit snug
so it doesn't slide.

181
00:22:14.916 --> 00:22:17.541
but not so tight that it
restricts your movement.

182
00:22:18.250 --> 00:22:19.416
Got it?

183
00:22:20.916 --> 00:22:22.416
How's that feel?

184
00:22:46.125 --> 00:22:47.916
All right. Zeb. drop us here.

185
00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:45.500
Yes?

186
00:23:45.583 --> 00:23:47.343
I'll take a flat-meat fry
for the little one.

187
00:23:47.416 --> 00:23:49.125
Got it. Okay. got it. got it.

188
00:23:49.208 --> 00:23:50.666
Flat-meat fry. huh?

189
00:23:53.208 --> 00:23:54.791
Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah.

190
00:24:01.041 --> 00:24:02.333
Whoa.

191
00:24:02.416 --> 00:24:04.083
That's quite an
impressive denomination.

192
00:24:04.166 --> 00:24:05.601
I'm not sure I've got
change for that.

193
00:24:05.625 --> 00:24:06.958
You can keep the change.

194
00:24:07.041 --> 00:24:08.666
I'm new to these parts.

195
00:24:08.750 --> 00:24:10.875
I can use some information.

196
00:24:10.958 --> 00:24:13.333
Yeah. for this price. I'll
tell you whatever you want.

197
00:24:13.833 --> 00:24:15.250
I'm looking for a Hutt.

198
00:24:15.333 --> 00:24:17.833
Shh. Don't mention that name.
Don't say that.

199
00:24:17.916 --> 00:24:19.392
What. are you trying
to get us both killed?

200
00:24:19.416 --> 00:24:21.500
Here. Keep your credits.
Food's on me.

201
00:24:22.041 --> 00:24:23.833
Go away. Thank you.

202
00:24:23.916 --> 00:24:26.500
Okay. never happened.
Let's go. Nothing to see here.

203
00:24:26.583 --> 00:24:28.166
Damn Mandalorian.
talking like that.

204
00:24:28.250 --> 00:24:30.500
Just out in the open.
he talks like... What is this?

205
00:24:30.583 --> 00:24:33.250
No. no. no. No. no. no. no.
I don't want your credits.

206
00:24:33.333 --> 00:24:34.809
'cause I didn't give you
any information.

207
00:24:34.833 --> 00:24:36.250
His name is Rotta.

208
00:24:37.125 --> 00:24:38.125
Really?

209
00:24:40.416 --> 00:24:41.666
Something funny?

210
00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:43.208
Yeah. yeah. Everybody...

211
00:24:43.291 --> 00:24:45.125
Everybody knows Rotta the Hutt.

212
00:24:45.208 --> 00:24:47.333
That guy's a monster.

213
00:25:33.583 --> 00:25:34.958
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

214
00:25:35.041 --> 00:25:37.208
He doesn't seem like
a prisoner to me.

215
00:25:39.291 --> 00:25:40.958
Rotta!

216
00:26:21.208 --> 00:26:22.750
Are you here to kill me?

217
00:26:23.625 --> 00:26:25.333
I'm here to rescue you.

218
00:26:27.458 --> 00:26:29.833
What makes you think
I need rescuing?

219
00:26:29.916 --> 00:26:31.791
Your aunt and uncle
hired me to find you.

220
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:37.000
Yeah. I see. Well. thank you.
but I don't require rescuing.

221
00:26:37.625 --> 00:26:40.041
Tomorrow's the last match
in my contract and after that.

222
00:26:40.125 --> 00:26:41.833
my debt will be paid.

223
00:26:41.916 --> 00:26:43.583
I'll be a free agent.

224
00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:48.333
Paid to who?

225
00:26:51.166 --> 00:26:52.166
Who's he?

226
00:26:53.291 --> 00:26:55.125
Don't stare.

227
00:26:55.208 --> 00:26:57.166
It's okay. What's your name?

228
00:26:57.250 --> 00:26:59.208
He doesn't talk.

229
00:26:59.291 --> 00:27:00.916
Who do you have to pay?

230
00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.375
Can I feed him?

231
00:27:06.375 --> 00:27:07.583
Sure.

232
00:27:07.666 --> 00:27:09.083
Who do you have to pay?

233
00:27:14.875 --> 00:27:16.291
Lord Janu.

234
00:27:17.666 --> 00:27:19.250
I don't know the name.

235
00:27:19.333 --> 00:27:20.708
You should.

236
00:27:20.791 --> 00:27:23.541
He runs the Syndicate
on all the moons of Shakari.

237
00:27:26.166 --> 00:27:27.583
He signed me to his stable.

238
00:27:27.666 --> 00:27:29.833
He bankrolled
my board and training.

239
00:27:29.916 --> 00:27:31.791
He keeps you in a cage.

240
00:27:31.875 --> 00:27:33.000
He treats me well.

241
00:27:33.541 --> 00:27:36.333
And after tomorrow night.
I'll be my own man.

242
00:27:36.416 --> 00:27:39.000
And with the following
he got me as a promoter.

243
00:27:39.083 --> 00:27:41.166
not only will my debt be paid.

244
00:27:41.250 --> 00:27:42.750
but I'll be rich
by the solstice.

245
00:27:42.833 --> 00:27:44.958
Grogu. heel!

246
00:27:47.750 --> 00:27:50.250
Don't worry. I'm not my father.

247
00:27:55.708 --> 00:27:58.083
You know how hard it is
to be your own man

248
00:27:58.166 --> 00:28:00.041
when your father is
Jabba the Hutt?

249
00:28:05.666 --> 00:28:08.083
You see them
cheering for me out there?

250
00:28:08.166 --> 00:28:09.166
For me.

251
00:28:09.916 --> 00:28:13.125
It's the first time
I'm not living in his shadow.

252
00:28:13.208 --> 00:28:15.250
That's why I fight in the pits.

253
00:28:15.750 --> 00:28:19.041
They feared him.
but they cheer for me.

254
00:28:20.833 --> 00:28:22.083
So. no...

255
00:28:22.791 --> 00:28:24.666
I don't need to be rescued.

256
00:28:28.666 --> 00:28:30.416
Where can I find Lord Janu?

257
00:28:32.125 --> 00:28:34.000
Thank you. Closed for the night.

258
00:28:38.833 --> 00:28:41.000
What the hell's he thinking?
Damn Mandalorians.

259
00:28:41.083 --> 00:28:42.726
Mandalorians. they don't even
come from here.

260
00:28:42.750 --> 00:28:44.333
He's going around. talking...

261
00:28:45.583 --> 00:28:48.583
I just wanna know
where I can find Lord Janu.

262
00:28:48.666 --> 00:28:51.916
Don't say that.
Do not say that name.

263
00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:53.541
Stop saying it.

264
00:28:53.625 --> 00:28:55.750
I recommend you calm down.

265
00:28:56.291 --> 00:28:57.976
Just. please. please.
don't kill me. Don't kill me.

266
00:28:58.000 --> 00:28:59.833
I've got... I've got
12 little ones at home.

267
00:28:59.916 --> 00:29:01.958
smaller than him.
It's... They're smaller.

268
00:29:02.791 --> 00:29:04.750
Yeah. it's just...

269
00:29:04.833 --> 00:29:07.208
I pay him protection. okay?

270
00:29:07.291 --> 00:29:08.291
We all do.

271
00:29:08.375 --> 00:29:09.916
I barely make a living.
to be honest.

272
00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:12.416
-But at least I'm alive.
-Who collects for him?

273
00:29:12.500 --> 00:29:14.166
I don't know.
Different people come in.

274
00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:16.392
Sometimes they come here.
sometimes I do a drop myself.

275
00:29:16.416 --> 00:29:17.958
-What do I know?
-Where?

276
00:29:18.041 --> 00:29:20.750
-Where what?
-Where do you do the drops?

277
00:29:20.833 --> 00:29:22.208
I don't... Some pla...
Sometimes.

278
00:29:22.291 --> 00:29:24.208
I go down to... different places.

279
00:29:24.291 --> 00:29:26.250
Usually... Sometimes
I go to the salt bar

280
00:29:26.333 --> 00:29:28.125
under Korvin Station.

281
00:29:28.208 --> 00:29:30.166
And then there's
other places too. You go to...

282
00:29:30.250 --> 00:29:31.916
You know. You know. I go around.

283
00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:35.375
No. I don't want it.
I don't want it.

284
00:29:35.458 --> 00:29:36.833
I didn't give you
any information.

285
00:29:36.916 --> 00:29:38.916
-I was just talking.
-That's not for information.

286
00:29:39.208 --> 00:29:40.416
It's to cover his tab.

287
00:30:26.250 --> 00:30:27.750
I'm looking for Lord Janu.

288
00:30:32.375 --> 00:30:34.291
Maybe you made a mistake.

289
00:30:36.250 --> 00:30:38.916
Maybe you remember wrong
and think you know me.

290
00:30:42.458 --> 00:30:44.666
Maybe you just walked through
the wrong door.

291
00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:48.375
Well. I'm not here to buy salt.

292
00:30:49.166 --> 00:30:50.375
Salt?

293
00:30:51.208 --> 00:30:52.583
We don't sell salt.

294
00:30:53.500 --> 00:30:54.625
It's on the ration.

295
00:30:57.083 --> 00:30:59.083
How much for the shoulder candy?

296
00:31:01.958 --> 00:31:03.833
Would look real pretty
in a cage.

297
00:31:04.916 --> 00:31:06.583
I'm here to see Lord Janu.

298
00:31:07.875 --> 00:31:09.958
I won't repeat myself again.

299
00:31:58.750 --> 00:32:01.041
It seems you've
earned your salt today.

300
00:32:04.208 --> 00:32:05.250
I'm Janu.

301
00:32:06.333 --> 00:32:08.291
Come to the back
and pick out a crystal.

302
00:32:08.791 --> 00:32:09.791
Hogsbreth.

303
00:32:11.625 --> 00:32:13.166
have the boys clean up.

304
00:32:14.458 --> 00:32:16.583
Make sure I don't lose any pets.

305
00:32:35.250 --> 00:32:36.250
Here.

306
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:38.166
Choose one.

307
00:32:38.250 --> 00:32:40.875
Salt is of no value to me
where I'm from.

308
00:32:40.958 --> 00:32:42.958
But here
it's worth a small fortune.

309
00:32:43.041 --> 00:32:46.291
because it's rationed
by the politicians.

310
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:48.500
Which makes it rare.

311
00:32:49.958 --> 00:32:51.625
As are you. Mandalorian.

312
00:32:53.208 --> 00:32:55.291
Have you ever considered
fighting in the pits?

313
00:32:55.375 --> 00:32:57.375
I try to avoid violence.

314
00:32:58.791 --> 00:33:00.000
'Course you do.

315
00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:02.208
I do as well.

316
00:33:04.041 --> 00:33:05.708
So what brings you to
this establishment

317
00:33:05.791 --> 00:33:07.375
if you're not
in the market for salt?

318
00:33:07.458 --> 00:33:10.416
I wanna buy out the contract
on a fighter from your stable.

319
00:33:11.041 --> 00:33:13.708
Perhaps you would consider
joining my stable instead?

320
00:33:19.875 --> 00:33:22.416
This buys a lot of salt
where I'm from.

321
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:23.666
I am offering you this

322
00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:26.541
in exchange for the fighting
contract on Rotta the Hutt.

323
00:33:26.625 --> 00:33:28.666
My dear boy.
there's no price high enough

324
00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:30.875
to buy him out of
his last fights.

325
00:33:30.958 --> 00:33:33.166
I've been grooming that
little prince for many cycles.

326
00:33:33.250 --> 00:33:34.875
setting him up
for tomorrow's match.

327
00:33:34.958 --> 00:33:36.000
Take the credits.

328
00:33:36.083 --> 00:33:38.291
It's his last fight
for you anyway.

329
00:33:39.416 --> 00:33:40.666
It's his last fight ever.

330
00:33:42.291 --> 00:33:43.809
I've collected
the most deadly creatures

331
00:33:43.833 --> 00:33:45.333
from across the galaxy.

332
00:33:45.875 --> 00:33:47.833
He's fighting a Dejarik match?

333
00:33:48.375 --> 00:33:49.500
Yes.

334
00:33:50.208 --> 00:33:51.791
He will die tomorrow.

335
00:33:52.958 --> 00:33:54.458
And a select few know it.

336
00:33:55.333 --> 00:33:56.666
Here's my gift to you:

337
00:33:57.708 --> 00:33:58.708
take those credits.

338
00:34:00.166 --> 00:34:02.000
bet it all
on the death of the Hutt.

339
00:34:02.875 --> 00:34:04.291
In exchange.

340
00:34:04.375 --> 00:34:07.916
all I ask is that you
consider fighting in my pit.

341
00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:10.166
The people of Shakari
would pay any price

342
00:34:10.250 --> 00:34:12.125
to see the rarest of sights.

343
00:34:12.208 --> 00:34:15.000
one of the legendary
Mandalorian warriors

344
00:34:15.083 --> 00:34:17.458
engaging in blood sport.

345
00:34:26.125 --> 00:34:27.541
This should more than cover

346
00:34:28.125 --> 00:34:30.083
our little misunderstanding
out there.

347
00:34:34.041 --> 00:34:36.166
All I ask
is that you consider my offer.

348
00:34:37.875 --> 00:34:40.166
Could make us both very rich.

349
00:35:14.458 --> 00:35:17.291
Looks like we're gonna have to
do this the hard way.

350
00:36:46.041 --> 00:36:47.416
What?

351
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:50.041
Janu's planning on killing you.

352
00:36:50.125 --> 00:36:51.250
I'm here to get you out.

353
00:36:54.583 --> 00:36:57.500
Tomorrow's my last fight.
I'll be free after I win.

354
00:36:57.583 --> 00:37:00.958
The fix is in.
It's a Dejarik match.

355
00:37:01.041 --> 00:37:02.708
He will keep
throwing opponents at you

356
00:37:02.791 --> 00:37:03.875
until you die.

357
00:37:03.958 --> 00:37:05.708
Why should I believe you?

358
00:37:06.208 --> 00:37:08.541
You were sent by my aunt
and uncle who want me dead.

359
00:37:08.625 --> 00:37:10.250
They want you back.

360
00:37:10.333 --> 00:37:11.791
You're embarrassing them.

361
00:37:11.875 --> 00:37:12.958
The Twins want me dead

362
00:37:13.041 --> 00:37:15.625
because I'm heir
to the throne. not them.

363
00:37:15.708 --> 00:37:17.250
But I don't want it.

364
00:37:17.333 --> 00:37:19.708
I don't wanna be anything
like my father.

365
00:37:20.750 --> 00:37:23.833
When I first started fighting.
the people all booed me.

366
00:37:23.916 --> 00:37:25.375
They wanted to see me die

367
00:37:25.458 --> 00:37:27.541
because I'm the son
of Jabba the Hutt.

368
00:37:27.625 --> 00:37:29.416
Then I won and became a champion

369
00:37:29.500 --> 00:37:31.583
and they slowly began to cheer.

370
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:33.666
They realized I'm not my father.

371
00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:35.166
I'm my own man.

372
00:37:35.250 --> 00:37:37.583
and I'm not afraid to fight
for what I have.

373
00:37:37.666 --> 00:37:40.500
To earn it.
To prove myself to everyone.

374
00:37:41.416 --> 00:37:44.041
Kid. fighting's not a sport.

375
00:37:44.125 --> 00:37:45.958
It's a last resort.

376
00:37:46.041 --> 00:37:48.125
Now come with me
before things get ugly.

377
00:37:48.208 --> 00:37:50.541
Guards. he's back!

378
00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:57.000
Get out. Get out!

379
00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:44.291
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

380
00:39:04.333 --> 00:39:06.250
<i>Rotta!</i>

381
00:39:33.333 --> 00:39:34.750
I don't want to fight you.

382
00:39:35.666 --> 00:39:37.708
Then you're in for a long day!

383
00:39:47.166 --> 00:39:48.208
Yes!

384
00:40:13.791 --> 00:40:16.541
I'm not going to kill you.

385
00:40:16.625 --> 00:40:18.333
I'm here to rescue you.

386
00:41:05.083 --> 00:41:07.375
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

387
00:41:07.458 --> 00:41:10.166
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

388
00:41:10.250 --> 00:41:12.875
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

389
00:41:12.958 --> 00:41:15.750
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

390
00:41:15.833 --> 00:41:18.208
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

391
00:41:18.291 --> 00:41:20.041
Kill! Kill! Kill...

392
00:41:20.125 --> 00:41:21.291
I yield.

393
00:41:25.875 --> 00:41:27.958
Rotta the Hutt has won.

394
00:41:28.041 --> 00:41:30.708
Now you owe him his freedom.

395
00:41:37.750 --> 00:41:39.833
Rotta the Hutt has won.

396
00:41:40.583 --> 00:41:42.500
Now he is free...

397
00:41:45.166 --> 00:41:46.291
to die!

398
00:42:32.041 --> 00:42:34.833
Our only chance
is to work together.

399
00:43:59.041 --> 00:44:00.791
Watch out for the little one.

400
00:44:00.875 --> 00:44:02.166
Yeah. I got this.

401
00:45:13.250 --> 00:45:14.250
We should go now.

402
00:45:14.333 --> 00:45:15.500
Now!

403
00:45:45.791 --> 00:45:46.791
Are you good?

404
00:45:48.291 --> 00:45:50.708
Don't worry. buddy.
We're getting out of here.

405
00:46:13.625 --> 00:46:15.833
You were right. The fix was in.

406
00:46:15.916 --> 00:46:17.375
Let's get you out of here.

407
00:46:19.125 --> 00:46:20.750
I'm gonna find us a ride.

408
00:46:43.041 --> 00:46:44.291
Sorry. Mando.

409
00:46:44.375 --> 00:46:45.833
I can't go back.

410
00:47:09.208 --> 00:47:11.041
Zeb. I got a runner.

411
00:48:01.500 --> 00:48:03.708
Okay. you got me.

412
00:48:04.750 --> 00:48:06.666
Can't blame a guy for trying.

413
00:48:24.666 --> 00:48:26.875
We're about
to jump to hyperspace.

414
00:48:26.958 --> 00:48:28.375
Where are you bringing me?

415
00:48:28.458 --> 00:48:30.208
It's not safe
to keep you chained up.

416
00:48:30.708 --> 00:48:31.916
If I unlock you.

417
00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:33.958
can we agree to no funny stuff?

418
00:48:34.041 --> 00:48:36.083
Are you bringing me
to Nal Hutta?

419
00:48:36.166 --> 00:48:37.250
This is an old ship.

420
00:48:37.333 --> 00:48:39.250
Sometimes things
get a little bouncy.

421
00:48:39.833 --> 00:48:42.125
My aunt and uncle
were scared of my father.

422
00:48:42.208 --> 00:48:44.208
They've always been cruel to me.

423
00:48:44.291 --> 00:48:46.416
Now that they control
his criminal empire.

424
00:48:46.500 --> 00:48:48.166
they need me eliminated.

425
00:48:48.250 --> 00:48:50.333
You bring me to them.
I'm a dead man.

426
00:48:50.416 --> 00:48:51.458
You don't know that.

427
00:48:51.541 --> 00:48:52.625
If you let me go.

428
00:48:52.708 --> 00:48:54.458
you'll never hear from me again.

429
00:48:54.958 --> 00:48:56.625
It's a big galaxy.

430
00:48:56.708 --> 00:48:57.916
I can disappear.

431
00:48:58.000 --> 00:48:59.666
Sorry. kid.

432
00:48:59.750 --> 00:49:01.333
I was hired to do a job.

433
00:49:01.916 --> 00:49:04.125
I don't know how
you sleep at night.

434
00:49:04.208 --> 00:49:05.791
working for those monsters.

435
00:49:06.333 --> 00:49:08.166
I don't work for them.

436
00:49:08.250 --> 00:49:10.291
I work for the New Republic.

437
00:49:10.375 --> 00:49:12.791
They hired me. not the Twins.

438
00:49:13.291 --> 00:49:14.916
When I bring you back.
they're giving me

439
00:49:15.000 --> 00:49:16.708
the whereabouts
of Commander Coin.

440
00:49:16.791 --> 00:49:19.750
a high-ranking ex-Imperial
operating on the Outer Rim.

441
00:49:20.250 --> 00:49:21.541
It's Janu.

442
00:49:22.666 --> 00:49:25.541
The man you're looking for
is Janu.

443
00:49:25.625 --> 00:49:27.000
Lord Janu Coin.

444
00:49:27.500 --> 00:49:29.017
That's who the Hutts
are gonna give you.

445
00:49:29.041 --> 00:49:30.333
He's ex-Imperial.

446
00:49:30.416 --> 00:49:32.750
That can't be.
The Twins would've told me.

447
00:49:32.833 --> 00:49:34.458
I saw stormtroopers.

448
00:49:35.375 --> 00:49:37.000
He brought me to his estate once

449
00:49:37.083 --> 00:49:38.166
to celebrate a big win

450
00:49:38.250 --> 00:49:40.500
and there were
stormtroopers everywhere.

451
00:49:40.583 --> 00:49:42.543
If you don't believe me
and you don't get him now.

452
00:49:42.625 --> 00:49:44.041
you won't get another shot.

453
00:49:44.541 --> 00:49:46.208
In fact.
it might already be too late.

454
00:49:47.083 --> 00:49:48.625
That's quite a story.

455
00:49:48.708 --> 00:49:50.416
Why should I believe you?

456
00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:53.541
You're a bounty hunter.
you know when someone's lying.

457
00:49:55.916 --> 00:49:57.500
Am I lying...

458
00:49:57.583 --> 00:49:59.250
or am I telling the truth?

459
00:50:19.958 --> 00:50:21.083
That's it.

460
00:50:21.666 --> 00:50:23.583
That's Janu Coin's compound.

461
00:50:24.416 --> 00:50:27.000
Could be big boy's
telling the truth.

462
00:50:27.083 --> 00:50:29.750
The place is lousy
with stormtroopers.

463
00:50:33.208 --> 00:50:34.416
How many did you see

464
00:50:34.500 --> 00:50:35.500
when you were in there?

465
00:50:36.458 --> 00:50:37.458
A lot.

466
00:50:38.541 --> 00:50:39.875
You're gonna need
a lot of backup

467
00:50:39.958 --> 00:50:41.791
if you're actually
thinking of going in.

468
00:50:42.708 --> 00:50:43.833
Uh-huh.

469
00:50:45.125 --> 00:50:47.083
Get word
to all our foot soldiers

470
00:50:47.166 --> 00:50:49.083
on the dark side of Shakari.

471
00:50:49.166 --> 00:50:52.833
I want eyes on the star port
and all the freight lanes.

472
00:50:52.916 --> 00:50:53.916
Lean on the mayor.

473
00:50:54.000 --> 00:50:56.250
Nothing takes off
or lands until we find them.

474
00:50:56.333 --> 00:50:58.416
Muster
my personal security forces.

475
00:50:59.041 --> 00:51:01.250
We're going to hit the streets
in full armor.

476
00:51:01.333 --> 00:51:02.613
I don't want to take any chances

477
00:51:02.666 --> 00:51:04.041
when it comes to
The Mandalorian.

478
00:51:04.125 --> 00:51:06.416
I've heard many things
about those monsters.

479
00:51:06.916 --> 00:51:08.250
It's all true.

480
00:51:09.750 --> 00:51:11.916
Imperial Commander Janu Coin.

481
00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:13.750
I'm here on behalf
of the New Republic

482
00:51:13.833 --> 00:51:15.375
to bring you to justice.

483
00:51:16.000 --> 00:51:18.500
I'm afraid we're outside
of your jurisdiction.

484
00:51:19.250 --> 00:51:20.541
Take him!

485
00:51:25.375 --> 00:51:26.958
-Set blasters on full.
-Hurry!

486
00:52:26.250 --> 00:52:28.083
I can bring you in warm...

487
00:52:29.666 --> 00:52:31.583
or I can bring you in cold.

488
00:52:55.583 --> 00:52:56.958
<i>Grogu.</i>

489
00:52:58.500 --> 00:52:59.625
<i>Rotta.</i>

490
00:53:00.333 --> 00:53:01.791
<i>Rotta. come in.</i>

491
00:53:01.875 --> 00:53:03.250
<i>Does anyone read me?</i>

492
00:53:04.833 --> 00:53:06.041
I'm up. I'm up.

493
00:53:06.125 --> 00:53:08.291
<i>I need you
to fire up the drives.</i>

494
00:53:08.375 --> 00:53:09.458
<i>Fire up the drives.</i>

495
00:53:09.541 --> 00:53:11.291
<i>-We have company.</i>
-Received.

496
00:53:12.041 --> 00:53:14.375
I don't know how to fly.
Do you know how to fly?

497
00:53:15.166 --> 00:53:16.833
Neither of us know how to fly.

498
00:53:16.916 --> 00:53:18.625
and I can't even
fit in the cockpit.

499
00:53:25.125 --> 00:53:28.500
Grogu. I need you to go
to the control panel.

500
00:53:28.583 --> 00:53:30.583
Remember the buttons
I told you never to touch?

501
00:53:30.666 --> 00:53:32.291
<i>I'm gonna need you
to touch them.</i>

502
00:53:32.375 --> 00:53:35.125
<i>Look for
the ignition relay cutoff.</i>

503
00:53:35.208 --> 00:53:37.333
<i>It's next to
the fuel differential readout.</i>

504
00:53:37.875 --> 00:53:40.666
<i>which is between
the pump compression gauge</i>

505
00:53:40.750 --> 00:53:42.541
<i>and the primary reserve indic...</i>

506
00:53:45.125 --> 00:53:46.541
Whoa.

507
00:53:46.625 --> 00:53:49.125
No. Don't touch
the missile battery switch.

508
00:53:49.208 --> 00:53:50.833
<i>That's why there's
a safety guard on it.</i>

509
00:53:50.916 --> 00:53:53.041
<i>Do you see
the fuel readout display?</i>

510
00:53:53.125 --> 00:53:54.583
Remember I showed you that one?

511
00:53:54.666 --> 00:53:55.833
<i>It's on the other side</i>

512
00:53:55.916 --> 00:53:58.250
<i>of the manual control
surface calibration un...</i>

513
00:54:00.958 --> 00:54:02.833
I don't think
he knows what he's doing.

514
00:54:25.208 --> 00:54:26.333
Get out.

515
00:54:30.875 --> 00:54:33.375
Get going.
They're shooting at you too.

516
00:54:41.750 --> 00:54:43.708
Good job. buddy. Strap in.

517
00:55:08.375 --> 00:55:09.916
I like this kid.

518
00:55:20.583 --> 00:55:22.416
Come on. Come on.

519
00:55:34.666 --> 00:55:36.541
Get us out of atmosphere
and jump!

520
00:55:36.625 --> 00:55:37.666
Get up here.

521
00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:39.750
I need you to bypass
the exhaust restrictors.

522
00:55:53.583 --> 00:55:56.000
This old junker's
gonna get us killed.

523
00:55:56.083 --> 00:55:57.208
I need more power.

524
00:55:57.291 --> 00:55:59.958
Disable the safety panel
so I can override the limiter.

525
00:56:00.041 --> 00:56:02.708
How? I'm a pilot. not a meknek.

526
00:56:02.791 --> 00:56:04.916
Just rip out
the whole brain board.

527
00:56:10.416 --> 00:56:12.000
Everything okay up there?

528
00:56:12.083 --> 00:56:13.500
Perfect.

529
00:56:20.208 --> 00:56:22.958
I told you to strap in.
Always wear your seat belt.

530
00:56:32.375 --> 00:56:34.250
Take it easy up there!

531
00:56:40.625 --> 00:56:41.958
There we go.

532
00:58:13.791 --> 00:58:15.625
That doesn't look like a Hutt.

533
00:58:15.708 --> 00:58:18.416
This is Imperial Commander
Janu Coin.

534
00:58:18.500 --> 00:58:21.666
He's full of information and
ready to sing like a Yuzzum.

535
00:58:21.750 --> 00:58:23.416
Isn't that right. Coin?

536
00:58:23.500 --> 00:58:24.916
I demand an attorney be present

537
00:58:25.000 --> 00:58:26.166
if I'm to be questioned.

538
00:58:26.833 --> 00:58:27.833
You see?

539
00:58:28.333 --> 00:58:30.041
He's full of secrets.

540
00:58:30.875 --> 00:58:32.666
You were supposed
to bring back Rotta.

541
00:58:33.791 --> 00:58:36.041
We had an arrangement
with the Twins.

542
00:58:36.125 --> 00:58:38.208
This is your Ace of Staves.

543
00:58:38.958 --> 00:58:40.958
This is who they were
going to lead you to.

544
00:58:41.666 --> 00:58:42.791
And then tip him off.

545
00:58:42.875 --> 00:58:45.500
sell you out and collect
credits from both sides.

546
00:58:46.708 --> 00:58:48.083
Take him away.

547
00:58:53.166 --> 00:58:55.083
Intelligence
has been cultivating

548
00:58:55.166 --> 00:58:58.333
a relationship with the Hutts
for a very long time.

549
00:58:58.416 --> 00:58:59.916
and you crossed them.

550
00:59:01.375 --> 00:59:03.166
The Twins can hold a grudge.

551
00:59:03.250 --> 00:59:04.500
I made a call.

552
00:59:04.583 --> 00:59:06.208
I got you the big prize.

553
00:59:06.750 --> 00:59:08.708
The Twins can rot in hell.

554
00:59:08.791 --> 00:59:10.226
Well. you missed out
on them paying you

555
00:59:10.250 --> 00:59:12.208
a big bounty for their nephew.

556
00:59:12.291 --> 00:59:13.416
Hmm...

557
00:59:13.500 --> 00:59:14.791
So be it.

558
00:59:16.791 --> 00:59:18.833
Well. I'll see if
I can hit up Command

559
00:59:18.916 --> 00:59:20.833
for a fee
for the capture of Coin.

560
00:59:20.916 --> 00:59:23.416
Don't worry about it.
It's on me.

561
00:59:24.208 --> 00:59:25.791
This one got messy.

562
00:59:25.875 --> 00:59:27.125
I'm taking a break.

563
00:59:28.708 --> 00:59:30.041
I understand.

564
00:59:31.083 --> 00:59:32.291
Mando.

565
00:59:34.958 --> 00:59:36.208
Good job.

566
01:01:00.583 --> 01:01:02.583
We're gonna
pull the restrict or plates.

567
01:01:02.666 --> 01:01:05.333
The first one should be
just past the return line.

568
01:01:05.416 --> 01:01:06.916
That's it.

569
01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:09.125
There should be three more.

570
01:01:21.708 --> 01:01:24.000
Okay. okay. Okey-doke.

571
01:01:30.125 --> 01:01:31.125
Okay. okay.

572
01:01:31.208 --> 01:01:32.541
Thanks for coming.

573
01:01:33.208 --> 01:01:34.500
No problem.

574
01:01:34.583 --> 01:01:37.375
I'm looking to make some
performance modifications.

575
01:01:37.458 --> 01:01:39.250
I need to cut out
dead weight for speed.

576
01:01:40.666 --> 01:01:43.000
Pull out anything
that doesn't make her go.

577
01:01:43.833 --> 01:01:44.833
Hey!

578
01:01:44.916 --> 01:01:46.250
Hey. Hey.

579
01:01:46.333 --> 01:01:47.333
No. don't touch me!

580
01:01:47.416 --> 01:01:49.750
Heel.

581
01:01:49.833 --> 01:01:51.541
-The horrible baby.
-The bad baby.

582
01:01:51.625 --> 01:01:53.583
Stay.

583
01:01:53.666 --> 01:01:55.000
I purged the fuel lines.

584
01:01:55.083 --> 01:01:56.750
I wanna remove
all the restrictors

585
01:01:56.833 --> 01:01:58.416
and unplug the exhaust.

586
01:01:58.500 --> 01:02:01.583
-Got it. Yeah. yeah.
-No problem. Yeah. I got it.

587
01:02:02.208 --> 01:02:03.458
-No problem.
-Yeah. Okey-doke.

588
01:02:04.916 --> 01:02:06.166
You wanna go help them?

589
01:02:08.041 --> 01:02:09.791
Do you promise to play nice?

590
01:02:11.166 --> 01:02:13.250
All right. Go.

591
01:02:19.875 --> 01:02:21.000
Don't worry about him.

592
01:02:23.375 --> 01:02:25.125
Little guy's gonna be okay.

593
01:02:27.291 --> 01:02:29.291
Sorry. I found these
in your kitchen.

594
01:02:33.125 --> 01:02:34.916
I was alone when I was his age.

595
01:02:35.791 --> 01:02:37.333
I had to fend for myself.

596
01:02:42.708 --> 01:02:43.958
He's lucky he has you.

597
01:02:44.833 --> 01:02:47.708
Well. you didn't
turn out half bad.

598
01:02:49.125 --> 01:02:52.750
Mmm. Life's messy.
but we do the best we can.

599
01:02:54.333 --> 01:02:56.000
Listen. I called a gunrunner

600
01:02:56.083 --> 01:02:57.833
who agreed to take you
out of the system.

601
01:02:57.916 --> 01:02:59.791
We both know the Twins
will be looking for you.

602
01:02:59.875 --> 01:03:01.250
so you best keep moving.

603
01:03:26.458 --> 01:03:27.833
Thank you. Mando.

604
01:03:27.916 --> 01:03:29.375
It was a fair trade.

605
01:03:29.458 --> 01:03:31.375
Make sure you lay low.

606
01:03:31.458 --> 01:03:33.791
I don't wanna see your name
on my list again.

607
01:03:33.875 --> 01:03:35.083
You have my word.

608
01:03:36.208 --> 01:03:38.458
All right. you take care
of yourself. little guy.

609
01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:42.916
And keep an eye on
your old man. too. all right?

610
01:03:43.916 --> 01:03:45.291
Here you go.

611
01:03:45.375 --> 01:03:47.083
Hang on to these for me.

612
01:04:28.250 --> 01:04:30.583
Let's save the rest of these
for after dinner.

613
01:05:48.333 --> 01:05:50.208
Wake up.

614
01:05:50.291 --> 01:05:51.291
Oh. What? Uh.

615
01:05:51.375 --> 01:05:52.708
-Wake up.
-What's going on?

616
01:05:52.791 --> 01:05:54.041
There's someone out there.

617
01:05:54.125 --> 01:05:55.583
I'll be awake in the morning.

618
01:05:55.666 --> 01:05:57.500
Quiet. Get under the floor.

619
01:06:09.416 --> 01:06:12.708
Wait here. If I signal. get out.

620
01:06:33.500 --> 01:06:35.875
Shh. Shh. Shh.

621
01:07:23.958 --> 01:07:27.041
Help! It got me! It got me!

622
01:07:27.125 --> 01:07:29.333
Keibu.

623
01:08:22.250 --> 01:08:24.416
Did you get the Mandalorian?

624
01:08:25.666 --> 01:08:29.458
Very good. Bring him to Nal Hutta.

625
01:08:37.541 --> 01:08:39.083
Help me! Help!

626
01:09:39.458 --> 01:09:41.666
Ow.

627
01:09:43.208 --> 01:09:45.458
Ow. ow. ow.

628
01:09:47.333 --> 01:09:48.583
Let him go.

629
01:09:55.458 --> 01:09:57.208
Hey. you hungry?

630
01:10:01.458 --> 01:10:02.958
You want a treat?

631
01:10:04.791 --> 01:10:06.208
Here you go.

632
01:10:06.291 --> 01:10:08.083
Good girl.

633
01:10:09.375 --> 01:10:10.375
Come on. Come on!

634
01:10:10.458 --> 01:10:12.500
Uh-oh.

635
01:10:12.583 --> 01:10:13.916
Oh.

636
01:10:33.625 --> 01:10:35.291
Uh-oh.

637
01:10:40.333 --> 01:10:41.958
Who hired you?

638
01:10:42.708 --> 01:10:44.166
Was it the Hutts?

639
01:10:45.708 --> 01:10:47.291
Well. if it was the Hutts.

640
01:10:47.375 --> 01:10:49.458
I'd make sure they're
paying you what you're worth.

641
01:10:49.541 --> 01:10:51.208
But I'm guessing a Kyuzo
is smart enough

642
01:10:51.291 --> 01:10:52.491
to get their money up-front...

643
01:12:49.291 --> 01:12:51.291
Nal Hutta.

644
01:12:51.375 --> 01:12:54.583
The Hutts are there.
I don't like it.

645
01:13:14.416 --> 01:13:16.208
Oh! Wow! Oh. I'm coming.

646
01:13:24.125 --> 01:13:25.333
Kid. don't be scared.

647
01:13:25.416 --> 01:13:27.166
Don't be scared.
It's okay. yeah.

648
01:13:27.250 --> 01:13:28.333
Come on. let's go.

649
01:13:28.416 --> 01:13:30.125
Oh...

650
01:13:40.541 --> 01:13:43.625
Oh! Hello!
It's me. it's me! You're here.

651
01:13:43.708 --> 01:13:46.416
You came for me! You found me!

652
01:13:47.750 --> 01:13:49.458
Oh. we thought you were dead.

653
01:13:50.416 --> 01:13:52.000
Mandalorian. he saved me.

654
01:13:52.083 --> 01:13:54.125
Big guy. He's inside there.

655
01:13:54.208 --> 01:13:56.083
Yeah. we got to go and find him

656
01:13:56.166 --> 01:13:57.958
and bring him home for the baby.

657
01:13:59.833 --> 01:14:02.791
The big thing. The big dog.
The big dog. The big...

658
01:14:02.875 --> 01:14:04.875
Oh. oh. It picked me up...

659
01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:18.541
Mando is in there.
In the palace.

660
01:14:31.291 --> 01:14:32.958
Come on. Up. up. up. up.

661
01:14:33.041 --> 01:14:34.875
Come on. baby. You can do it.

662
01:14:43.166 --> 01:14:44.916
Big pipe. huh?

663
01:15:13.291 --> 01:15:14.791
Good shot. baby.

664
01:15:37.041 --> 01:15:39.458
Pay the hunter.

665
01:15:55.041 --> 01:15:58.208
You broke our agreement.

666
01:15:58.291 --> 01:16:00.458
Now you must pay.

667
01:16:01.250 --> 01:16:02.916
Bring me his helmet.

668
01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:15.875
Mandalorian steel.

669
01:16:15.958 --> 01:16:19.666
Priceless on the black market.

670
01:16:21.041 --> 01:16:24.458
But worth even more is knowing

671
01:16:24.541 --> 01:16:28.250
we have shamed you forever.

672
01:16:28.875 --> 01:16:31.625
We know the Mandalorian Creed.

673
01:16:32.166 --> 01:16:33.916
You will be outcast

674
01:16:34.000 --> 01:16:37.416
for letting an enemy see
your face.

675
01:16:38.083 --> 01:16:39.708
Not if you all die.

676
01:16:43.416 --> 01:16:46.791
It will bring us ecstasy

677
01:16:46.875 --> 01:16:51.708
to watch
your strong spirit break.

678
01:17:00.791 --> 01:17:01.791
Monsters.

679
01:17:02.500 --> 01:17:04.208
You did this to him.

680
01:17:04.291 --> 01:17:07.583
Rotta would have
died painlessly.

681
01:17:07.666 --> 01:17:09.083
but you betrayed us.

682
01:17:09.583 --> 01:17:13.083
Now he will suffer
for centuries.

683
01:17:13.625 --> 01:17:18.666
You see. Hutts live for
hundreds of years.

684
01:17:19.458 --> 01:17:24.000
Just like
your small. green child.

685
01:17:24.500 --> 01:17:26.583
One day you will die.

686
01:17:26.666 --> 01:17:30.541
and Grogu will be without you
to protect him.

687
01:17:30.625 --> 01:17:34.500
And then.
it will be his turn to suffer.

688
01:20:27.291 --> 01:20:29.875
You have entertained us.

689
01:20:30.666 --> 01:20:32.916
Here is your reward.

690
01:22:31.916 --> 01:22:33.916
Uh-oh. Which way?

691
01:23:38.458 --> 01:23:42.166
Even if
you win. you will die from the poison.

692
01:24:08.291 --> 01:24:09.416
<i>Dank farrik.</i>

693
01:24:12.750 --> 01:24:14.000
Get out! Go!

694
01:24:16.125 --> 01:24:18.125
Come on. go! Go. go!

695
01:24:32.666 --> 01:24:35.500
-Oh. yeah!
-Wow!

696
01:24:35.583 --> 01:24:36.958
Wait. Wait.

697
01:25:05.375 --> 01:25:07.041
You okay?

698
01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:15.416
-How did you get here?
-We got a ship.

699
01:25:15.500 --> 01:25:16.958
That way. Let's go!

700
01:25:23.583 --> 01:25:27.333
Send the droids!
Release the Amani! Don't let him escape!

701
01:25:53.000 --> 01:25:54.791
This way. This way. yeah.

702
01:26:06.875 --> 01:26:08.666
This way!

703
01:26:15.083 --> 01:26:16.833
Up. up. up. up. going up!

704
01:26:16.916 --> 01:26:18.833
I don't want to fall.
I don't want to.

705
01:26:19.541 --> 01:26:20.541
Go!

706
01:26:20.625 --> 01:26:22.750
Yeah. Okay. okay. Yeah.
Let's go.

707
01:26:35.583 --> 01:26:37.958
Go. kid.
I can't fit in that thing.

708
01:26:39.250 --> 01:26:41.000
but you have to leave.

709
01:26:43.541 --> 01:26:44.750
Don't worry.

710
01:26:45.375 --> 01:26:47.083
I'll be right behind you.

711
01:26:51.250 --> 01:26:53.666
Go now. I'll hold them off.

712
01:26:54.208 --> 01:26:56.125
We'll come back for you. Mando.

713
01:26:59.958 --> 01:27:01.208
Come on. baby.

714
01:27:01.291 --> 01:27:03.166
Don't worry. We'll be back.

715
01:27:03.250 --> 01:27:05.500
Yeah. let's go. Let's go.

716
01:27:05.583 --> 01:27:06.750
Come on. baby.

717
01:28:37.666 --> 01:28:39.041
Goodbye. kid.

718
01:31:33.041 --> 01:31:34.833
No life force detected.

719
01:37:32.416 --> 01:37:35.125
Methinks you are
the one who stole my fish.

720
01:37:49.208 --> 01:37:51.875
I'm guessing
you're not from around here.

721
01:37:55.833 --> 01:37:58.833
A morsel like you
should be more careful.

722
01:37:58.916 --> 01:38:02.416
You look to be the bottom
of the Nal Hutta food chain.

723
01:38:03.916 --> 01:38:05.958
I'm surprised
you haven't found your way

724
01:38:06.041 --> 01:38:07.791
to the Hutts' supper table.

725
01:38:10.375 --> 01:38:12.208
You've heard of the Hutts.
have you?

726
01:38:13.416 --> 01:38:14.666
Are you scared?

727
01:38:16.458 --> 01:38:17.583
You should be.

728
01:38:18.083 --> 01:38:21.041
They would swallow you whole
given half a chance.

729
01:38:25.541 --> 01:38:27.333
Make yourself scarce.

730
01:38:50.166 --> 01:38:51.166
Uh-huh.

731
01:39:26.125 --> 01:39:27.291
Hey.

732
01:39:29.166 --> 01:39:30.583
Get away from my fish.

733
01:39:35.791 --> 01:39:37.416
Keibu.

734
01:39:58.000 --> 01:40:00.000
The hunter says
you have a partner.

735
01:40:01.625 --> 01:40:04.541
Says you two escaped the Twins.

736
01:40:04.625 --> 01:40:06.500
Well. that's impressive.

737
01:40:12.166 --> 01:40:14.875
Says your partner's
hurt real bad.

738
01:40:14.958 --> 01:40:18.208
Bit by a dragon snake. Poisoned.

739
01:40:22.375 --> 01:40:24.666
I want you to feed this to him.

740
01:40:26.958 --> 01:40:27.958
Now. you should know.

741
01:40:28.041 --> 01:40:30.125
this might be too little.
too late.

742
01:40:30.625 --> 01:40:33.375
and there's a good chance
he doesn't wake up.

743
01:40:37.791 --> 01:40:39.791
Either way.
best thing you can do

744
01:40:39.875 --> 01:40:41.458
right now
is make him comfortable.

745
01:40:42.416 --> 01:40:45.583
There comes a time where
we all have to say goodbye.

746
01:40:52.833 --> 01:40:55.250
I wish you luck. small traveler.

747
01:43:43.000 --> 01:43:44.041
Hey. kiddo.

748
01:43:49.833 --> 01:43:51.166
The old protect the young.

749
01:43:51.250 --> 01:43:53.041
and then the young
protect the old.

750
01:43:54.166 --> 01:43:55.500
This is the Way.

751
01:43:58.666 --> 01:44:00.333
Now how do we
get off this planet?

752
01:44:07.500 --> 01:44:10.041
That's the gunrunner
that was carrying Rotta.

753
01:46:24.708 --> 01:46:28.416
Well. kid. the way I see it
we got two choices.

754
01:46:29.125 --> 01:46:31.583
We can use this ship.
Get off world.

755
01:46:32.250 --> 01:46:34.750
That might buy us some time.
A little bit of peace.

756
01:46:35.250 --> 01:46:37.458
But the Hutts
will keep coming for us.

757
01:46:38.541 --> 01:46:40.291
Just like they came for Rotta.

758
01:46:43.416 --> 01:46:44.500
So. do we run?

759
01:46:48.791 --> 01:46:49.875
Or do we fight?

760
01:47:33.875 --> 01:47:35.666
Huh?

761
01:47:51.583 --> 01:47:53.375
Repel the intruders!

762
01:47:53.458 --> 01:47:54.958
Roger. roger!

763
01:47:55.625 --> 01:47:57.041
Protect the palace!

764
01:47:57.125 --> 01:47:58.125
Affirmative.

765
01:48:07.583 --> 01:48:08.708
Follow my lead.

766
01:48:13.125 --> 01:48:14.208
Fire!

767
01:48:25.166 --> 01:48:26.750
Come on. Come on.

768
01:49:05.500 --> 01:49:07.041
On me.

769
01:49:50.708 --> 01:49:51.708
Fall back!

770
01:52:28.250 --> 01:52:30.333
Wait! We know much.

771
01:52:30.416 --> 01:52:31.916
Go help Rotta.

772
01:52:40.125 --> 01:52:41.666
You saw my face.

773
01:52:42.583 --> 01:52:43.583
Stop!

774
01:52:44.333 --> 01:52:45.833
Now it's time to die.

775
01:53:54.875 --> 01:53:55.958
Leave him alone!

776
01:54:18.125 --> 01:54:20.916
You don't have Jabba to protect you.

777
01:54:21.500 --> 01:54:22.958
I'm not little anymore!

778
01:55:54.208 --> 01:55:57.458
Stop! You'll kill us all!

779
01:56:42.000 --> 01:56:43.541
Save us. bounty hunter!

780
01:56:44.916 --> 01:56:45.916
Keibu.

781
01:56:46.000 --> 01:56:47.666
Save us!

782
01:57:22.000 --> 01:57:24.666
We don't have much time.
We have to get out of here.

783
01:57:25.625 --> 01:57:26.833
Is there another way out?

784
01:57:26.916 --> 01:57:29.583
-I think it's that way.
-Go. Go!

785
01:57:46.083 --> 01:57:47.083
Target sighted.

786
01:58:13.000 --> 01:58:13.916
Hello?

787
01:58:14.000 --> 01:58:15.875
<i>Mando! We came back.</i>

788
01:58:15.958 --> 01:58:17.208
-What?
-We came back.

789
01:58:17.291 --> 01:58:19.000
We told you we would.

790
01:58:26.041 --> 01:58:29.000
<i>Adelphi Squadron.
entering atmosphere.</i>

791
01:58:29.958 --> 01:58:32.666
-What's your status. Mando?
<i>-We're under attack.</i>

792
01:58:33.666 --> 01:58:35.000
There are too many.

793
01:58:35.083 --> 01:58:37.083
Fire everything you have
at my location.

794
01:58:38.625 --> 01:58:41.833
<i>-Your location?</i>
-Yes. my location.

795
01:58:41.916 --> 01:58:43.416
I can't give that order.

796
01:58:43.500 --> 01:58:44.916
Don't worry...

797
01:58:46.916 --> 01:58:49.125
we'll be out of here
by the time you do.

798
01:58:50.750 --> 01:58:51.791
Good luck.

799
01:58:55.375 --> 01:58:56.666
Blue Leader to squadron.

800
01:58:57.250 --> 01:59:00.291
<i>assume defensive formation.
prepare to engage.</i>

801
01:59:00.375 --> 01:59:01.541
All weapons hot.

802
01:59:01.625 --> 01:59:02.625
Copy that.

803
01:59:20.083 --> 01:59:21.833
Enemy fighters approaching.

804
01:59:24.000 --> 01:59:25.000
Here they come.

805
01:59:52.166 --> 01:59:53.500
Turbolasers. up ahead.

806
01:59:53.583 --> 01:59:54.750
Got it.

807
02:00:15.625 --> 02:00:17.041
I've got one on my tail.

808
02:00:19.750 --> 02:00:21.250
I got you.

809
02:00:31.416 --> 02:00:33.041
Yippee! Yay!

810
02:00:33.125 --> 02:00:34.708
Taking out the launch tubes.

811
02:00:42.458 --> 02:00:45.333
Blue Leader to Red Jammer.
mark it and lock it in.

812
02:00:47.833 --> 02:00:48.958
Locking in target.

813
02:00:52.666 --> 02:00:53.708
It's a dead end.

814
02:00:55.000 --> 02:00:56.416
We're trapped.

815
02:00:57.125 --> 02:00:58.333
Stand back.

816
02:01:04.708 --> 02:01:06.041
<i>We're closing fast.</i>

817
02:01:06.125 --> 02:01:07.541
Repeat. we're closing fast.

818
02:01:07.625 --> 02:01:09.208
You better be
out of there. Mando.

819
02:01:09.291 --> 02:01:10.708
Jump.

820
02:01:10.791 --> 02:01:12.875
That's a long way down.

821
02:01:12.958 --> 02:01:14.166
Closing on target.

822
02:01:15.708 --> 02:01:18.000
-Gotta jump.
-Moat's not that deep.

823
02:01:18.083 --> 02:01:20.125
It's a bomber. Jump.

824
02:01:20.208 --> 02:01:22.000
Let's light up this swamp.

825
02:01:56.791 --> 02:01:58.416
<i>Anybody got eyes on Mando?</i>

826
02:01:59.083 --> 02:02:00.083
There they are.

827
02:02:04.500 --> 02:02:08.250
Zeb. go collect the trash.

828
02:02:16.375 --> 02:02:19.166
I'm getting a little tired
of these hot extractions.

829
02:02:20.083 --> 02:02:22.041
What took you so long?

830
02:02:23.375 --> 02:02:24.500
Hop in.

831
02:02:24.583 --> 02:02:26.416
Let's head home.

832
02:02:49.333 --> 02:02:50.708
Colonel.

833
02:02:53.041 --> 02:02:54.416
Messy.

834
02:02:55.000 --> 02:02:56.250
Very messy.

835
02:02:57.458 --> 02:02:59.083
Why'd you come for me?

836
02:02:59.166 --> 02:03:00.666
That wasn't part of the mission.

837
02:03:01.416 --> 02:03:04.541
You were right.
Coin told us everything.

838
02:03:05.041 --> 02:03:06.666
The Twins were playing us.

839
02:03:06.750 --> 02:03:09.291
Feeding information
to the Empire all along.

840
02:03:10.625 --> 02:03:13.291
They picked a side.
It wasn't ours.

841
02:03:13.916 --> 02:03:17.541
Besides.
we don't leave our own behind.

842
02:03:18.083 --> 02:03:19.875
I'm an independent contractor.

843
02:03:19.958 --> 02:03:22.916
Sure. Mando. Sure you are.

844
02:03:33.583 --> 02:03:35.500
Can I give you a ride somewhere?

845
02:03:35.583 --> 02:03:37.791
Actually. I was thinking
I could stay here.

846
02:03:38.583 --> 02:03:40.375
Maybe work for the New Republic.

847
02:03:40.958 --> 02:03:43.375
Don't take this
the wrong way. but...

848
02:03:43.458 --> 02:03:45.541
I'm not sure you would fit in.

849
02:03:45.625 --> 02:03:47.458
You know...

850
02:03:47.541 --> 02:03:49.791
I might have
a uniform that would fit him.

851
02:03:50.833 --> 02:03:53.708
Come on. let me buy you a drink.

852
02:03:55.500 --> 02:03:58.041
Thank you. Mando.
I owe you big time.

853
02:03:58.125 --> 02:03:59.458
Just doing my job.

854
02:04:00.083 --> 02:04:01.083
And keep an eye on him.

855
02:04:02.208 --> 02:04:03.833
Your dad's one of the good ones.

856
02:04:18.291 --> 02:04:19.583
Come on. big guy.

857
02:04:20.750 --> 02:04:23.125
Watch your step.
First round's on me.

858
02:04:32.291 --> 02:04:34.416
Hey. kid. Come up here.

859
02:04:54.083 --> 02:04:55.291
Your turn.

860
02:04:58.208 --> 02:04:59.208
Go ahead.
